snippet.textDisplay:
You say its meaningless but its all about perseverance and knowing what to do when you get backup again.

I am a casual Dark Souls player but I watched a video of a dud explaining why the games can be so important to some people. In summary, Souls games can be ruthless yet they are not unfair. One is presented with a hard challenge that seems impossible at the beginning but as you keep playing, as you keep reviving, you get farther and farther ahead, little by little, learning and understanding how to handle the situation until you manage to defeat the boss which makes you feel like the big bad dog who rules.

Such thing can be said about life too, since we wake up every day in a new day with a lot of choices to make. Some people choose to lay down and give up, but this game was able to make them feel that they too can be able to overcome the hardship of life with willpower, to be able to stand up again even when it seems impossible.
